{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015SJEXtUuXgWHDUULBKs1Wg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture! \n\nThe case resource defines a StatefulSet with:\n1. `cert-selector` init container that picks either `ca1` or `ca2` certs based on pod name\n   - `es-cluster-0` and `es-cluster-1` get ca1 cert\n   - `es-cluster-2` gets ca2 cert\n2. An `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/transport-ca`\n3. The `transport-cert` emptyDir volume at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs`\n   \nBut the currently running cluster is actually from a previous stage using Elasticsearch 8.11.1 with HTTP TLS certs from `es-http-tls`, no cert-selector init container, and a completely different volume configuration. The precondition was skipped because it found 6 pods already running, so it only created the transport CA bundle configmap rather than deploying the case-specific cluster. The actual cluster in place doesn't match what this case expects at all. The fixture created the `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap, but the current StatefulSet doesn't actually reference it since it's using the older 8.11.1 http TLS setup. The oracle checks are looking for the configmap to exist with 2 certs, 3 nodes in the cluster, and yellow/green status—which might already be satisfied by what's been set up so far.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1463,"cache_read_input_tokens":45905,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1463},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd016cd2-1b8e-4fb8-a177-2ff3ecad8fee","uuid":"858db9ea-9ba6-47b7-927c-5d69e45b1355","request_id":"req_011CcLz8NPEqtD4EjdZ7TU2P"}
